definition:
Someone descended from Hamul who was a man of the tribe of Judah living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.12; 
 son of: Perez (H6557); 
 brother of: Hezron (H2696H)
Group of cha.mul (חָמוּל "Hamul" H2538) 
 § Hamulites = "spared"
 descendants of Hamul, grandson of Judah by Tamar
